section.section:
The comprehensive plan shall address at least the following issues:
integration of public and private funding sources;
maximization of federal funding opportunities;
consideration of the special needs of disabled children, including needed services, supports, and appropriate provider training;
promotion of the use of school buildings and local public transportation resources for after-school and summer opportunity programs;
where needed, technical assistance for compliance with the Maryland Out of School Time Programs' Quality Standards Framework;
promotion of continued expansion of high quality after-school and summer opportunity programs in the State; and
integration of any plans developed by local jurisdictions.
